Use the standard library
This is how to prod_signs of arr:
   When arr's length is 0, then:
      The answer is []
   End when

   Remember that negatives is 0
   Remember that zeros is 0
   Remember that i is 0

   Do this arr's length times:
      When item i in arr is 0, then:
         Increase zeros
      But, if not:
         When item i in arr is less than 0, then:
            Increase negatives
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do

   When zeros is more than 0, then:
      The answer is [0]
   End when

   When remainder of negatives and 2 is 0, then:
      The answer is [9]
   But, if not:
      The answer is [-9]
   End when
Now you know